OL,4,Camid NHS 'national emergency', nurses
OL,5,Cwarn
OL,7,F"Receiving a cancer diagnosis in a
OL,8,Fpublic area isn't care. It's a
OL,9,Fnightmare for all involved. We need to
OL,10,Fcall it out as nursing staff, and
OL,11,Fhealth leaders and ministers need to
OL,12,Ftake responsibility."
OL,14,FOne nurse, working in a hospital in
OL,15,FEngland, said: "Patients are soiled
OL,16,Ffor long periods of time because there
OL,17,Fis nowhere to change them. I've
OL,18,Fwitnessed DNACPR (do not attempt
OL,19,Fcardiopulmonary resuscitation)
OL,20,Fdecisions being signed in the corridor.
