OL,7,F"I've had to move a deceased patient
OL,8,Finto a corridor in order to generate
OL,9,Fresus (resuscitation) capacity before.
OL,10,FIt's horrific."
OL,12,FNursing staff revealed that corridor
OL,13,Fcare has become the norm in almost
OL,14,Fevery corner of a typical hospital
OL,15,Fsetting.
OL,17,FProf Ranger will say: "Treating
OL,18,Fpatients in corridors used to be an
OL,19,Fexceptional circumstance. Now it is a
OL,20,Fregular occurrence and a symptom of a
OL,21,Fsystem in crisis.
